      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALNAIR (5) was solid two back on the Illawarra Grange track before winning last time out to 1890m at Newcastle. Getting out to 2150m now looks a good move and Keagan Latham makes the trip with her. The form out of her last start has been franked and she can repeat the dose. LITTLE LUNCH (9) switched from the Kurt Goldman stable to Jarrod Austin two back and hasn't been disgraced in two provincial efforts recently. Back to country grade now is a big tick as is Collett's booking. Can sit handy from the inside barrier and she can improve again. TOD (6) steps straight out to 2150m third-up into the campaign after getting well back and not featuring at Moruya last time out. Chad Lever hops on board and he still has plenty of upside. IT IS TO BE (4) got caught in a slowly run affair here last start. Is sure to make an impression if there's more tempo this time. HARDAZHELL (7) can feature in the finish once again.",
